{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CubemapArray","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"s are made of an array of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap"},{"text":"s. Like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"s, they are made of multiple textures, the amount of which must be divisible by 6 (one for each face of the cube).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The primary benefit of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray","type":"reference"},{"text":"s is that they can be accessed in shader code using a single texture reference. In other words, you can pass multiple ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap"},{"type":"text","text":"s into a shader using a single "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray"},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"s are allocated in adjacent cache regions on the GPU, which makes ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray"},{"type":"text","text":"s the most efficient way to store multiple "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","isActive":true,"type"